<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="310" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,423,835,897]" box="[151,217,871,897]" pageId="5" pageNumber="310">
<figureCitation box="[151,217,871,897]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1863,1887]" captionTargetBox="[152,1429,181,1839]" captionTargetId="figure-20@7.[151,1435,181,1839]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Vespa simillima specimen collected at Shawnigan Lake, British Columbia, Canada. A. Dorsal habitus. B. Lateral habitus. C. Anterior view of head. D. Fore wings. Scale bars: 1 mm. Pt = pterostigma. Dashed line in D is the prestigma." pageId="5" pageNumber="310">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,943,1545]" pageId="5" pageNumber="310">
The specimen identified as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="1868" box="[471,650,943,969]" class="Insecta" family="Vespidae" genus="Vespa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="310" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="simillima">
<emphasis box="[471,650,943,969]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="310">Vespa simillima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[669,739,943,969]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1863,1887]" captionTargetBox="[152,1429,181,1839]" captionTargetId="figure-20@7.[151,1435,181,1839]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Vespa simillima specimen collected at Shawnigan Lake, British Columbia, Canada. A. Dorsal habitus. B. Lateral habitus. C. Anterior view of head. D. Fore wings. Scale bars: 1 mm. Pt = pterostigma. Dashed line in D is the prestigma." pageId="5" pageNumber="310">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
) was re-confirmed morphologically using the key of Smith-Pardo 
<emphasis box="[223,280,979,1005]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="310">et al.</emphasis>
(2020). Both primer pairs were successful in amplifying the COI gene, resulting in a 596 bp assembled sequence (GenBank Accession 
<accessionNumber box="[510,637,1015,1041]" httpUri="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nucleotide/OL702714" pageId="5" pageNumber="310">OL702714</accessionNumber>
). A GenBank BLAST found this sequence was 99.83% identical (one base pair different) to a 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="1868" box="[427,605,1051,1077]" class="Insecta" family="Vespidae" genus="Vespa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="310" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="simillima">
<emphasis box="[427,605,1051,1077]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="310">Vespa simillima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
specimen from 
<collectingCountry box="[791,933,1051,1078]" name="South Korea" pageId="5" pageNumber="310">South Korea</collectingCountry>
(Accession 
<accessionNumber box="[1075,1204,1051,1077]" httpUri="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nucleotide/KY172037" pageId="5" pageNumber="310">KY172037</accessionNumber>
), with an E value of 0.0 and bit-score of 1096. Including the Canadian specimen, there are 28 sequences of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="1868" box="[1145,1278,1087,1113]" class="Insecta" family="Vespidae" genus="Vespa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="310" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="simillima">
<emphasis box="[1145,1278,1087,1113]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="310">V. simillima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the BOLD database from 
<collectingCountry box="[320,462,1123,1150]" name="South Korea" pageId="5" pageNumber="310">South Korea</collectingCountry>
(16), 
<collectingCountry box="[533,597,1124,1150]" name="Japan" pageId="5" pageNumber="310">Japan</collectingCountry>
(9), 
<collectingCountry box="[654,733,1123,1149]" name="Russia" pageId="5" pageNumber="310">Russia</collectingCountry>
: 
<collectingRegion box="[745,921,1123,1149]" country="Russia" name="Primorskiy" pageId="5" pageNumber="310">Primorsky Krai</collectingRegion>
(1) and one of unstated country (
<accessionNumber box="[1305,1429,1123,1149]" httpUri="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nucleotide/KF933080" pageId="5" pageNumber="310">KF933080</accessionNumber>
) published in 
<bibRefCitation author="Perrard, A. &amp; Pickett, K. M. &amp; Villemant, C. &amp; Kojima, J. &amp; Carpenter, J." box="[295,520,1159,1185]" pageId="5" pageNumber="310" pagination="1 - 15" refId="ref7699" refString="Perrard, A., Pickett, K. M., Villemant, C., Kojima, J. &amp; Carpenter, J. (2013) Phylogeny of hornets: a total evidence approach (Hymenoptera, Vespidae, Vespinae, Vespa). Journal of Hymenoptera Research, 32, 1 - 15. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.3897 / JHR. 32.4685" type="journal article" year="2013">
Perrard 
<emphasis box="[384,439,1159,1185]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="310">et al.</emphasis>
(2013)
</bibRefCitation>
that was collected in 
<collectingCountry box="[761,825,1160,1186]" name="Japan" pageId="5" pageNumber="310">Japan</collectingCountry>
(Perrard, pers. comm.). All sequences are grouped in a single BIN (ACB8610) with a maximum sequence divergence between species of 1.77%.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
