<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="310" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,943,1545]" pageId="5" pageNumber="310">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1303,1329]" pageId="5" pageNumber="310">Distribution</emphasis>
: Southeast Asia including 
<collectingCountry box="[647,758,1304,1330]" name="Myanmar" pageId="5" pageNumber="310">Myanmar</collectingCountry>
, parts of 
<collectingCountry box="[862,932,1303,1329]" name="China" pageId="5" pageNumber="310">China</collectingCountry>
, eastern 
<collectingCountry box="[1030,1107,1303,1329]" name="Russia" pageId="5" pageNumber="310">Russia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1119,1190,1304,1330]" name="South Korea" pageId="5" pageNumber="310">Korea</collectingCountry>
, and 
<collectingCountry box="[1249,1316,1304,1330]" name="Japan" pageId="5" pageNumber="310">Japan</collectingCountry>
, adventive in northwest Nearctic (
<bibRefCitation author="Cannings, R. A." box="[407,581,1339,1365]" pageId="5" pageNumber="310" pagination="91" refId="ref6691" refString="Cannings, R. A. (1989) An Asian Hornet, Vespa simillima xanthoptera (Hymenoptera: Vespidae) in North America. Journal of the Entomological Society of British Columbia, 86, 91. [https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / page / 47087601  page / 99 / mode / 1 up]" type="journal article" year="1989">Cannings 1989</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="310" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,943,1545]" pageId="5" pageNumber="310">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,314,1375,1401]" pageId="5" pageNumber="310">Diagnosis</emphasis>
: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="1868" box="[330,507,1375,1401]" class="Insecta" family="Vespidae" genus="Vespa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="310" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="simillima">
<emphasis box="[330,507,1375,1401]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="310">Vespa simillima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from other 
<taxonomicName box="[882,1037,1375,1401]" pageId="5" pageNumber="310">
<emphasis box="[882,947,1376,1401]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="310">Vespa</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
that have been recorded in 
<collectingCountry box="[1352,1436,1375,1401]" name="Canada" pageId="5" pageNumber="310">Canada</collectingCountry>
by a combination of the following characters: 1) length of gena less than 1.6× length of eye at midheight in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[220,307,1447,1473]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1863,1887]" captionTargetBox="[152,1429,181,1839]" captionTargetId="figure-20@7.[151,1435,181,1839]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Vespa simillima specimen collected at Shawnigan Lake, British Columbia, Canada. A. Dorsal habitus. B. Lateral habitus. C. Anterior view of head. D. Fore wings. Scale bars: 1 mm. Pt = pterostigma. Dashed line in D is the prestigma." pageId="5" pageNumber="310">Fig. 4B</figureCitation>
), 2) pretegular carina incomplete, not spanning the height of the pronotal lobe, 3) female clypeus with punctures medially shallow, separated by one puncture diameter or more (
<figureCitation box="[987,1077,1483,1509]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1863,1887]" captionTargetBox="[152,1429,181,1839]" captionTargetId="figure-20@7.[151,1435,181,1839]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Vespa simillima specimen collected at Shawnigan Lake, British Columbia, Canada. A. Dorsal habitus. B. Lateral habitus. C. Anterior view of head. D. Fore wings. Scale bars: 1 mm. Pt = pterostigma. Dashed line in D is the prestigma." pageId="5" pageNumber="310">Fig. 4C</figureCitation>
); 4) male metasomal sterna 6–7 with posterior margin deeply emarginate medially.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
